-- Sebastien Loeb of France Wins World Rally Title for 7th Time, AFP Reports
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-10-03T15:03:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/sebastien-loeb-of-france-wins-world-rally-title-for-7th-time-afp-reports.html
Sebastien Loeb won the world rally
title for the seventh time after leading all the way in the
Rally of France, Agence France-Presse reported.  It was the Frenchman’s seventh consecutive world title, AFP
added. He’s won six of 11 rallies this season, with two legs
left.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  